identify the presence of alphanumeric characters and digits in string

> PROBLEM

You are given a string s.

Your task is to determine whether the string contains:

At least one alphanumeric character (a-z, A-Z, 0-9)
At least one alphabetical character (a-z, A-Z)
At least one digit (0-9)
At least one lowercase letter (a-z)
At least one uppercase letter (A-Z)
Input Format

A single line containing the string s.

Output Format

Print five lines:

True if the string contains at least one alphanumeric character; otherwise print False.
True if the string contains at least one alphabetical character; otherwise print False.
True if the string contains at least one digit; otherwise print False.
True if the string contains at least one lowercase character; otherwise print False.
True if the string contains at least one uppercase character; otherwise print False

Sample Input: qA2
Sample Output

True
True
True
True
True

>SOLUTION

if __name__ == '__main__':
    s = input()
    
    print(any(c.isalnum() for c in s))
    print(any(c.isalpha() for c in s))
    print(any(c.isdigit() for c in s))
    print(any(c.islower() for c in s))
    print(any(c.isupper() for c in s))
    
